Braille 'n Speak     --
    Blazie Engineering
     Mill Green Rd.
    Street, Md , U.S.A.

    (information provided by Doug Martin <martin@nosc.mil>)

    The Braille N Speak uses any of several Braille codes for entering
    information: Grade I, Grade II, or computer Braille.  Basically,
    letters a-j are combinations of dots , , , and .  Letters k-t are
    the same combinations as a-j with dot  added. Letters u, v, x, y, and
    z are like a-e with dots  and  added.  (w is unique because Louis
    Braille didn't have a w in the French alphabet.)


